### Phase 16a: Visual Foundation & Typography (SHORT-TERM - 2-4 weeks)

**Principle**: "Let content breathe; typography carries hierarchy, not color noise."

#### 1. Dark-First, Purposeful Color System
- [ ] **Audit current color usage** - Document all color decisions across components
- [ ] **Define semantic color palette** - 3-4 accent colors max (primary action, secondary, success, warning)
- [ ] **Dark mode as default scholar experience** - Deep, contemplative tones for extended study
- [ ] **Selective accent application** - Color only for interactive elements and status indicators
- **Implementation**: Update `globals.css` and Tailwind config with constrained palette
- **Done When**: No random color usage; every color has documented purpose

#### 2. Typographic Hierarchy Overhaul
- [ ] **Remove color-based hierarchy** - No "blue for headers, gray for body" patterns
- [ ] **Weight-based system** - Bold (700) for titles, Medium (500) for section headers, Regular (400) for body
- [ ] **Size scale refinement** - Establish 6-level type scale with clear purpose per level
- [ ] **Hebrew typography audit** - Ensure Hebrew fonts have equivalent hierarchy without relying on color
- **Implementation**: Create `typography.ts` design tokens, apply to `TopicExperience`, `TorahReader`
- **Done When**: User can understand content structure with page in grayscale

#### 3. Whitespace & Breathing Room
- [ ] **Component spacing audit** - Document current padding/margins in key components
- [ ] **Establish spacing scale** - 8px base unit, consistent multipliers (8, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64)
- [ ] **Section breathing room** - Minimum 48px between major content sections
- [ ] **Card internal spacing** - Generous padding (24px+) inside topic/source cards
- **Implementation**: Update `TopicExperience.tsx`, `TopicsList.tsx`, `SourcesTab.tsx`
- **Done When**: Content feels spacious, not cramped; no "wall of text" feeling

#### 4. Micro-Interactions & Subtle Animation
- [ ] **Hover state library** - Consistent hover effects for all interactive elements
- [ ] **Transition timing** - 150-200ms for UI feedback, 300ms for content transitions
- [ ] **Loading states** - Skeleton loaders that match content shape, not generic spinners
- [ ] **Focus indicators** - Clear but not jarring keyboard navigation feedback
- **Implementation**: Create `animations.ts` with Framer Motion presets, apply consistently
- **Done When**: App feels responsive and alive without being distracting

---

